FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1772503387
OL,3,CForeign Secretary defends decision to
OL,4,Callow US to use UK bases for Iran
OL,5,Cstrikes
OL,7,FThe Liberal Democrats have called for
OL,8,FMPs to be given a vote on the use of
OL,9,FUK bases for strikes on Iran.
OL,11,FLib Dem leader Sir Ed Davey said: "No
OL,12,Fmatter how the prime minister tries to
OL,13,Fredefine offensive as defensive, this
OL,14,Fis a slippery slope. He must not let
OL,15,FTrump drag Britain into another
OL,16,Fprolonged war in the Middle East.
OL,18,F"Starmer must come to Parliament
OL,19,Ftomorrow, set out the legal case in
OL,20,Ffull, and give MPs a vote."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1772503387
OL,3,CForeign Secretary defends decision to
OL,4,Callow US to use UK bases for Iran
OL,5,Cstrikes
OL,7,FWhile the leader of the Green Party,
OL,8,FZack Polanski, went further in
OL,9,Fcondemning the decision to let the US
OL,10,Fuse British bases, saying Starmer had
OL,11,Fjumped into "yet another Middle East
OL,12,Fillegal war".
OL,14,FReform UK leader Nigel Farage had
OL,15,Fcalled on Starmer to allow the US to
OL,16,Fuse UK bases before the government
OL,17,Fchanged its position, and said the
OL,18,Fdecision was "better late than never"
OL,19,Fbut described Starmer as "a follower,
OL,20,Fnot a leader".
OL,26,@sD@MOUtD@LO]zD@NOUzD@eO]{D@ZOU|D@MO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/9
